116.8	Homeschooling	Homeschooling	For much of history and in many cultures, enlisting professional teachers (whether as tutors or in a formal academic setting) was an option available only to a small elite. Thus, until relatively recently, the vast majority of people were educated by family members (especially during early childhood).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/Fireside_Education_frontispiece.jpg/200px-Fireside_Education_frontispiece.jpg
